oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Performance - Muhlenburg County Thumbpickers - 2012-07-07
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performances by guitar thumbpickers Joe Hudson, Paul Mosely, Eddie Pennington and Freddie Russell from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on July 7, 2012. Companion to a Chet Atkins exhibit.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Performances include; Sweet Georgia Brown; Walk Right Back (Freddie Russell); Eight More Miles To Louisville (Joe Hudson); Sweet Bunch Of Daisies (Paul Mosely); Mose's Blues (Eddie Pennington); Back To Old Smokey Mountain (Freddie Russell); Mystery Train (Joe Hudson); Back Up And Push (Paul Mosely); Texas Tornado (Eddie Pennington); Nine Pound Hammer (all); Mister Sandman (Freddie Russell); Jam Man/Windy And Warm (Joe Hudson); Back Home Again In Indiana (Paul Mosely); Merle's Dance (Eddie Pennington); Cannonball Rag (all); John Henry/I'll See You In My Dreams (all);
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Hudson, Joe; Mosely, Paul; Pennington, Eddie; Russell, Freddie; Muhlenburg County (Kentucky); Atkins, Chet; Country Music Hall of Fame & Museum (Nashville, Tenn.);
